{
  "texts": [
    "Let's test it with a specific angle.",
    "For example, \\(\\theta = 30^\\circ\\): \\(\\cos 30^\\circ = \\sqrt{3}/2\\), and \\(\\cos (180^\\circ -30^\\circ) = \\cos 150^\\circ = -\\sqrt{3}/2\\).",
    "These are not equal; in fact, they're negatives of each other.",
    "So, it seems there's an error in this paragraph.",
    "The correct identity involving \\(180^\\circ\\) is \\(\\cos (180^\\circ -\\theta) = -\\cos \\theta\\), not \\(\\cos \\theta\\). 1024"
  ]
}